Work Summary: Used K-Means Clustering to group customers based on spending patterns and income. 
By using the "Elbow Method," the optimal number of clusters ($K$) was identified to ensure the groups were distinct and meaningful.
4 Learning Outcomes:
Unsupervised Insight: Learned how to find "hidden groups" in data without using pre-defined labels.
Optimal $K$ Selection: Mastered the Elbow Method to balance model complexity with cluster accuracy.
Centroid Logic: Understood how the algorithm iteratively moves "center points" to define the heart of each customer persona.
Data-Driven Marketing: Developed the ability to translate mathematical clusters into actionable business segments (e.g., "High-Spenders" vs. "Bargain Hunters").
